HEADWORD: liquefied
<hw>liquefied</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>converted to a
liquid; <as>as, <ex>liquified</ex> natural gas; <ex>liquified</ex>
coal</as>.</def>.⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> liquified.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>rendered liquid by heating; changed from a solid to
a liquid state; melted.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> molten, liquified.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>rendered liquid by dissolution in a solvent; -- of
solids.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dissolved, liquified.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquefier</ent>⟦br⟧
